    <p><strong>Our recommendation for anxiety:</strong> Either KSM-66 or Sensoril will deliver clinically meaningful results. KSM-66 has the broader evidence base and is the extract used in most anxiety-specific trials. Sensoril has a higher withanolide concentration and may be slightly more potent per milligram for cortisol reduction specifically. Generic ashwagandha powder — listed simply as "ashwagandha root" or "ashwagandha root powder" without specifying KSM-66 or Sensoril — should be avoided. Without standardization, the withanolide content varies between batches, and no clinical trial has validated a specific dose of generic powder for anxiety.</p>

