    <!-- SECTION 4: CORRECT DOSAGE -->
    <h2>Correct Ashwagandha Dosage for Anxiety</h2>

    <p>Dosing is the single most important variable for anxiety outcomes — and the most common reason ashwagandha "does not work" for some people. The clinical trials that demonstrated significant anxiety reduction used specific doses of specific extracts. Replicating those doses is non-negotiable.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
      <span class="key-stat-num">600mg</span>
      <p class="key-stat-txt">of KSM-66 per day is the dose used in the landmark Chandrasekhar 2012 trial (300mg twice daily). <strong>This produced a 27.9% cortisol reduction and significant anxiety score improvement after 60 days.</strong> Most clinical trials use 300-600mg of KSM-66 daily — this is the evidence-based dosing range for anxiety.</p>
    </div>

